#### 8. Exception Handling in Tests — `ProcessOrder_EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` (line 105)

```csharp
try {
    processor.ProcessOrder(order);
    Assert.Fail("Expected an exception but none was thrown");
} catch (ValidationException ex) {
    Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
}
```

Manual try/catch duplicates what the framework provides. **Fix:** Use `Assert.ThrowsException`:

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ValidationException>(
    () => processor.ProcessOrder(order));
Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
```

*Note:* This is a capture-and-assert pattern (functional but ugly), not a swallowed exception — severity stays Medium.

